  "dateModified": "2026-04-02",
  "datePublished": "2026-04-02",
  "description": "Kurdish peoples are genred — reduced from a heteroglossic, multi-state, religiously diverse, politically sophisticated civilization to a set of consumable character templates — by four different states simultaneously. This paper traces how Iran, Turkey, Iraq, and the West each produce their own Kurdish genre figure, what those figures erase, and why the mechanism is uniquely unstable when applied to a people who keep contradicting the story.",
